cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes new techniques for Dynamic Ensemble Selection (DES) for classification tasks. The techniques are evaluated using experiments on 40 datasets, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. However, the paper also deals with imbalanced datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses techniques related to data mining (cs.DM) and neural networks (cs.NE), which further supports the possibility of these sub-categories.
